<div>
    <p>The SavedQuotations widget is different from most other widgets in that it doesn't work within the context of a quote, but
    instead creates its own context of a list of saved quotation. The form below can be used to add new saved quotations to the
    system which will appear in the SavedQuotations widget at the foot of the screen.</p>
    
	<div style="display:table; margin: 0px 350px;" >
        <div style="display:table-row">
            <div style="display:table-cell">Quotation number:</div>
            <div style="display:table-cell"><input value="" name="quotation-number-override" type="text"/></div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:table-row">
            <div style="display:table-cell">Quotation date override:</div>
            <div style="display:table-cell"><input value="dd/mm/yyyy" name="quotation-date-override" type="text"/></div>
        </div>
	    <div style="display:table-row">
	        <div style="display:table-cell">Expiry date override:</div>
	        <div style="display:table-cell"><input value="dd/mm/yyyy" name="expiry-date-override" type="text"/></div>
	    </div>
	    <div style="display:table-row">
	        <div style="display:table-cell">Premium override:</div>
	        <div style="display:table-cell"><input value="0.00" name="premium-override" type="text"/></div>
	    </div>
	</div>
</div>